40|$|In This {{paper we}} give an {{overview}} about our security framework {{developed in the}} ESPRIT Project FILIGRANE. The goal of this project is to develop an integrated security framework for mobile code commerce. The term mobile code includes all kind of mobile Java software (applets and agents and Java beans, cardlets etc.). Our framework has been developed {{to be used in}} the Internet and in particular in the World Wide Web. It is based on Smart Card, Public Key Cryptography and ERMS (<b>Electronic</b> <b>Right</b> <b>Management</b> System). The first integrated version of the FILIGRANE framework now exists and will be available shortly as a web Demonstrator. Keywords mobile agent security, <b>electronic</b> commerce, <b>electronic</b> <b>right</b> <b>management,</b> copyright protection, software piracy, reverse engineering 1. Introduction Reverse engineering, once the secret of experienced hackers, is going to be mainstream with Java. Software piracy has proved to be a very significant issue in the mobile code software business today. I [...] ...|$|R
